thread.title: Northeast Prepares for Second Storm in a Week

author: Paul Berger
title: Northeast Prepares for Second Storm in a Week
text:
The Northeast Wednesday prepared for a second winter storm in a week and one that forecasters predicted could bring one foot or more of wet, heavy snow and strong winds to some areas.
In New York City, though the morning started with a light rain, forecasters predicted precipitation would intensify later in the morning and turn to snow.
